'Crete' ( {{transl|gr|KrÃ­ti}}; ) is the largest and most populous of the Greek
islands, the fifth-largest island in the Mediterranean Sea, and one of the
thirteen administrative regions of Greece. It forms a significant part of the
economy and cultural heritage of Greece while retaining its own local cultural
traits (such as its own poetry, and music). Crete was once the center of the
Minoan civilization (), which is currently regarded as the earliest recorded
civilization in Europe. [http://oxfordbibliographiesonline.com/display/id/obo-9780195389661-
0071 Ancient Crete] Oxford Bibliographies Online: Classics
